# ğŸ“Œ 3ï¸âƒ£ Left Shift (<<)

### Concept

Left shift number ko 2 se multiply karta hai.

```
n << k  =  n Ã— (2^k)
```

### Example

```
5 = 101

5 << 1
101 â†’ 1010
= 10
```

### Why it works?

Binary me left shift karne se:

* Har bit ek position left move hota hai
* Right side me 0 add hota hai
* Value double ho jaati hai

### Time Complexity

O(1)

---

# ğŸ“Œ 4ï¸âƒ£ Right Shift (>>)

### Concept

Right shift number ko 2 se divide karta hai.

```
n >> k = n Ã· (2^k)
```

(integer division)

### Example

```
6 = 110

6 >> 1
110 â†’ 11
= 3
```

### Why it works?

Right shift last bit remove karta hai
Matlab divide by 2.

### Time Complexity

O(1)

---

# ğŸ“Œ 5ï¸âƒ£ Even / Odd Check

### Theory

Binary me last bit determine karta hai even ya odd.

| Last Bit | Number |
| -------- | ------ |
| 0        | Even   |
| 1        | Odd    |

### Logic

```
n & 1
```

### Why it works?

AND operator sirf last bit check karta hai.

---

# ğŸ“Œ 6ï¸âƒ£ Power of Two

### Theory

Power of 2 numbers ka binary form hota hai:

```
1000
100
10
1
```

Sirf ek bit set hoti hai.

### Logic

```
n & (n - 1)
```

### Why it works?

n - 1 karne se:

Rightmost set bit flip ho jaata hai.

Agar result 0 aaye â†’ sirf ek bit thi.

### Time Complexity

O(1)

---

# ğŸ“Œ 7ï¸âƒ£ Count Set Bits (Brian Kernighan)

### Theory

Har step me rightmost 1 remove karo.

### Logic

```
n = n & (n - 1)
```

### Why it works?

Ye operation lowest set bit hata deta hai.

### Time Complexity

O(number of set bits)

Better than O(log n)

---

# ğŸ“Œ 8ï¸âƒ£ Get i-th Bit

### Concept

Right shift karke last bit check karo.

```
(n >> i) & 1
```

---

# ğŸ“Œ 9ï¸âƒ£ Set i-th Bit

### Concept

```
n | (1 << i)
```

OR use karte hain bit ko 1 banane ke liye.

---

# ğŸ“Œ ğŸ”Ÿ Clear i-th Bit

### Concept

```
n & ~(1 << i)
```

NOT mask bana ke bit clear karte hain.

---

# ğŸ“Œ 1ï¸âƒ£1ï¸âƒ£ Toggle i-th Bit

### Concept

```
n ^ (1 << i)
```

XOR flip karta hai bit ko.

---

# ğŸ“Œ 1ï¸âƒ£2ï¸âƒ£ XOR Important Properties

```
a ^ a = 0
a ^ 0 = a
a ^ b ^ a = b
```

### Use Case

* Single number problem
* Missing number
* Swap without temp variable

---

# ğŸ“Œ 1ï¸âƒ£3ï¸âƒ£ Subsets Using Bitmask

### Theory

Agar n elements hain:

Total subsets =

```
2^n
```

Har number from 0 to (2^n - 1) ek subset represent karta hai.

### Why it works?

Binary representation element inclusion decide karta hai.

---

# ğŸ“Œ 1ï¸âƒ£4ï¸âƒ£ Fast Exponentiation (Binary Exponentiation)

### Theory

Exponent ko binary form me tod do.

Agar exponent ka bit 1 hai â†’ multiply karo.

### Time Complexity

O(log n)

---

# ğŸ“Œ 1ï¸âƒ£5ï¸âƒ£ Concatenation of Consecutive Binary Numbers

### Problem Idea

Binary string banana inefficient hai.

Instead:

```
R = (R << bits_of_i) + i
```

### Why it works?

Left shift jagah deta hai
Addition number ko attach karta hai

Ye actual binary concatenation hai.

### Time Complexity

O(n)

---

# ğŸ“Œ 1ï¸âƒ£6ï¸âƒ£ Complexity Summary

| Operation   | Complexity  |
| ----------- | ----------- |
| Left Shift  | O(1)        |
| Right Shift | O(1)        |
| Count Bits  | O(log n)    |
| Kernighan   | O(set bits) |
| Fast Power  | O(log n)    |
| Subsets     | O(2^n)      |

